    "industrial_process_notes": "Biologically synthesized by ribosomes translating mRNA (up to ~20 amino acids/second in prokaryotes) via peptide bond formation between the amino and carboxyl groups of successive amino acids. Short peptides can also be made industrially by chemical peptide synthesis, but this is inefficient beyond a few hundred residues. The term 'protein' was coined by Jöns Jacob Berzelius in 1838, building on Gerardus Johannes Mulder's elemental-composition work.",
